  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Peel and roughly chop your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Top, tail, peel and slice your <strong>carrot[s]</strong> into discs on the diagonal</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1710842505405-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1710842505405-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1710842505405-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1710842505405-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1710842505405-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine your <strong>cornflour</strong> and <strong>soy</strong> <strong>sauce</strong> in a bowl with <strong>half</strong> your <strong>honey</strong> (save the rest for later!), your <strong>toasted</strong> <strong>sesame</strong> <strong>oil</strong>, <strong>rice</strong> <strong>vinegar</strong> and 75ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[100ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[125ml]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water </strong>– this is your <strong>stir fry sauce</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1710842510439-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1710842510439-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1710842510439-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1710842510439-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1710842510439-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your<strong> white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 225ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold</strong> <strong>water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1710842518451-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1710842518451-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1710842518451-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1710842518451-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1710842518451-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, dry, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>cashew nuts</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until slightly toasted</p><p>Tip: Watch them like a hawk to make sure they don’t burn!</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1710842522873-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1710842522873-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1710842522873-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1710842522873-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1710842522873-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once slightly toasted, add the<strong> remaining</strong> <strong>honey</strong> to the pan with your <strong>chilli</strong> <strong>flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and cook for 2-3 min or until caramelised</p><p>Once caramelised, transfer the cashew nuts to a plate to cool into a brittle and reserve the pan – these are your <strong>honey chilli cashews</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1710842527461-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1710842527461-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1710842527461-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1710842527461-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1710842527461-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wipe the reserved pan clean and return to a high heat with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong></p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped</strong> <strong>onion</strong>, <strong>sliced</strong> <strong>carrot</strong> and <strong>sugar</strong> <strong>snap</strong> <strong>peas</strong> with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Once softened, add your <strong>pork mince </strong>(remove the paper if required!) to the pan<strong> </strong>and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to brown, breaking it up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1710842533684-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1710842533684-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1710842533684-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1710842533684-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1710842533684-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once browned, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and <strong>ginger</strong> <strong>paste</strong> and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>stir</strong> <strong>fry</strong> <strong>sauce</strong> and cook for a further 4 min or until the sauce has thickened and the pork is cooked through (no pink meat!)</p><p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>cooled</strong> <strong>honey chilli cashews</strong> roughly</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1710842540735-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1710842540735-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1710842540735-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1710842540735-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1710842540735-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>pork stir fry</strong> next to the <strong>cooked</strong> <strong>rice</strong></p><p>Garnish with the <strong>chopped honey chilli cashews</strong></p><p><strong><span class=\"text-danger\">Tip: Cooking for kids? Leave out the honey chilli cashews!</span></strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
      "media": {
        "images": []
      }
    }
